Table 1. Main results on COCO.  ? indicates that the results are on the COCO validation 2017 split. The rest results are on COCO test-dev. 
DISCOBOX with SOLOv2/ResNet-50 outperforms BBTP [47] by 10.3% on COCO validation 2017. Our best model achieves 37.9% mAP 
on test-dev, which outperforms some competitive supervised methods such as Mask R-CNN in absolute performance.

ous state-of-the-art methods on weakly supervised semantic corre-
spondence without bells-and-whistles.

Table 5. Results of multi-object correspondence on PASCAL 3D+, 
where AP0.75, AP1, AP1.5, AP2, and AP3 represent AP@? with 
thresholds ? ? {0.75%, 1%, 1.5%, 2%, 3%} relative to the box 
diagonal. AP is defined as mean(AP0.75, AP1, AP1.5, AP2, AP3).
